ix.gloss: the cardinal number that is the sum of eight and one
denoting a quantity consisting of one more than eight and one less than ten

ixia.gloss: a monocotyledonous genus of the family Iridaceae

ixodes.gloss: type genus of the family Ixodidae

ixodes dammini.gloss: a northeastern tick now recognized as same species as Ixodes scapularis

ixodes pacificus.gloss: a tick that feeds on dusky-footed wood rat and bites humans

ixodes ricinus.gloss: parasitic on sheep and cattle as well as humans

ixodes scapularis.gloss: parasitic on mice of genus Peromyscus and bites humans

ixodid.gloss: ticks having a hard shield on the back and mouth parts that project from the head
